\begin_layout Plain Layout
How do we keep the purity of a mixed state?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Purity can be measured as a function of 
\begin_inset Formula $t$
\end_inset

 by 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
p\left(t\right) & = & \text{Tr}\rho^{2}\\
 & = & \rho_{11}^{2}+\rho_{22}^{2}+2\left|\rho_{12}\right|^{2}\\
 & = & 1-2\rho_{11}\rho_{22}+2\left|\rho_{12}\right|^{2}
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset

To keep the purity, we need 
